section.definition:
L'ensemble $ℂ$ des nombres complexes est muni d'une addition et d'une multiplication définies par 
\Eq[*,C,r]{
\NC (x + iy) + (x' + iy') := x + x' + i(y + y')\HC{$+$}\NC\NR
\NC (x + iy) × (x' + iy') :=xx' - yy' + i(xy' + yx')\HC{$×$}\NC\NR
}

section.text:
L'addition (resp. la multiplication) est interne à $ℂ$ et admet $0$ (resp. $1$) comme élément neutre. 
Ainsi, pour $z$ et $z'$ dans $ℂ$, on a 
\Eq[C,c,C,r]{
\NC z+z' ∈ ℂ\NC et \NC zz' ∈ ℂ \HC{loi interne}\NC\NR
\NC 0 + z = z + 0 = x\NC et \NC 1z=z1=z \HC{élément neutre}\NC\NR
}

Chaque élément de $ℂ$ (resp. non nul) admet un unique inverse noté $-z$ (resp $1/z$) pour $+$ (resp. pour $×$) :
\Eq[C,r]{
\NC ∀ z∈ ℂ,∃!y∈ ℂ: y+z=z+y=0.\HC{$y=-z$ opposé de $z$}\NC\NR
\NC ∀ z∈ ℂ^*,∃!y∈ ℂ: yz=zy=1.\HC{$y=1/z$ inverse de $z$}\NC\NR
}

section.figure:
\starttikzpicture
\clip (-1,-1) rectangle (5.4,3.1);
\draw[blue!20,ultra thin] (-0.5,-0.5) grid (5.4,3.1);
\draw[-] (-0.5,0) -- (5,0) coordinate (x axis);
\draw[-] (0,-0.5) -- (0,3) coordinate (y axis);
\draw[-triangle 60,thick] (0,0) -- node [anchor=south,sloped] {$x\vec i+y\vec j$} node [anchor=north,sloped,pos=0.6,color=red] {$x+yi$} (4.3,2.4) node [anchor=south] {$M$};
\draw[-triangle 45,thick] (0,0) -- node [anchor=east,pos=0.65] {$y\vec j$} (0,2.4);
\draw[-triangle 45,thick] (0,0) -- node [anchor=north,pos=0.7] {$x\vec i$} (4.3,0);
\draw[dashed] (4.3,2.4) -- (0,2.4) node [color=red,anchor=south west] {$yi$};
\draw[dashed] (4.3,2.4) -- (4.3,0) node [color=red,anchor=south west] {$x$};
\draw[-open triangle 60,thick] (0,0) -- node [pos=0.4,anchor=east] {$\vec j$} (0,1);
\draw[-open triangle 60,thick] (0,0) -- node [pos=0.4,anchor=north] {$\vec i$} (1,0);
\node [anchor=north east] (O) at (0,0) {$O$};
\stoptikzpicture

section.text:
Géométriquement, l'addition de deux nombres complexes $s=a+ib$ et $z=c+id$ s'interprètre 
par la règle du parallèlogramme. Ainsi, sur la figure suivante, les points $O$, $M$, $P$ et $Q$, d'affixes~respectives $0$, $s$, $z$ et $s+z$, 
forment un parallèlogramme.

\starttikzpicture[scale=0.8]
\draw[-] (-0.2,0) -- (6.5,0) coordinate (x axis);
\draw[-] (0,-0.2) -- (0,4.5) coordinate (y axis);
\draw[-,thick,dotted] (2,2.5) -- (6,4) ;
\draw[-,thick,dotted] (4,1.5) -- (6,4);
\draw[-open triangle 60,thick] (0,0) -- node [pos=0.4,anchor=east] {$\vec j$} (0,1);
\draw[-open triangle 60,thick] (0,0) -- node [pos=0.4,anchor=north] {$\vec i$} (1,0);
\draw[-triangle 60,thick] (0,0) --  node [pos=0.7,sloped,anchor=south] {$s$} (2,2.5) node [anchor=south] {$M$};
\draw[dashed] (2,2.5) -- (0,2.5) node [color=red,anchor=east] {$b$};
\draw[dashed] (2,2.5) -- (2,0) node [color=red,anchor=north] {$a$};
\draw[-triangle 60,thick] (0,0) --  node [sloped,pos=0.7,anchor=north] {$z$} (4,1.5) node [anchor=west] {$P$};
\draw[dashed] (4,1.5) -- (0,1.5) node [color=red,anchor=east] {$d$};
\draw[dashed] (4,1.5) -- (4,0) node [color=red,anchor=north] {$c$};
\draw[-triangle 60,thick] (0,0) --  node [anchor=south,sloped,pos=0.5] {$s+z$} (6,4) node [anchor=south] {$Q$};
\draw[dashed] (6,4) -- (0,4) node [color=red,anchor=east] {$b+d$};
\draw[dashed] (6,4) -- (6,0) node [color=red,anchor=north] {$a+c$};
\node [anchor=north east] (O) at (0,0) {$O$};
\stoptikzpicture
